items.title: Lions quarterback Matthew Stafford called a play named for his buddy, Clayton Kershaw
items.summary: Lions QB Stafford calls play called 'Kershaw'
items.content: Surprisingly, it wasn't a wicked curve.

items.title: Kershaw disappointed after allowing first slam
items.summary: On Monday night, Clayton Kershaw had the postgame demeanor of the best pitcher in baseball no longer pitching like the best pitcher in baseball.

items.title: Altherr not taking slam off Kershaw for granted
items.summary: Phillies left fielder Aaron Altherr tried to treat Monday night's game against Dodgers ace Clayton Kershaw like any other. His efforts proved futile.

items.title: Knebel shows no sign of rust in Crew's win
items.summary: Corey Knebel pitched on Monday for the first time in six days -- and only the fifth time in 17 days -- to lock down the Brewers' 3-0 win over the Pirates at PNC Park

items.title: Mariners measure themselves against Astros
items.summary: As the Mariners watched the Astros celebrate their first division title since 2001 -- when Scott Servais was a backup catcher for Houston -- one thing was clear in the wake of Sunday's 7-1 loss.
